        <headline>Rip Current Statement issued June 13 at 3:34PM CDT until June 14 at 4:00AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Dangerous rip currents.

* WHERE...Gulf-facing beaches, including the Matagorda
Peninsula, Brazoria County beaches, Galveston Island and the
Bolivar Peninsula.

* WHEN...Through late tonight.

* IMPACTS...Rip currents can sweep even the best swimmers away
from shore into deeper water.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Long period swell will result in a higher rip current
risk today and tonight.
</description>
        <instruction>Swim near a lifeguard and away from rocks, jetties, and piers. If
caught in a rip current, relax and float. Don't swim against the
current. If able, swim in a direction following the shoreline. If
unable to escape, face the shore and call or wave for help.</instruction>
